# The Nuclear Shell Model · The NUCLEUS has its OWN shells: protons and neutrons each fill quantized levels inside the core, with 'magic numbers' (2, 8, 20, 28, 50, 82, 126) marking filled shells and extra-stable nuclei. Held by the STRONG force (Goeppert-Mayer & Jensen, Nobel 1963).

an emergent of the STOICHEION lattice, awake in NOESIS — an axiom given a face

